    '97b3899d-fdc4-5ca2-98b5-7fef0f48359e'::uuid,
    'arm_raises_t_y_i',
    'Arm Raises (T/Y/I)',
    '{"merged_steps": ["Stand upright with feet hip-width apart, core engaged, and arms relaxed at your sides.", "From this position, perform three different arm raises to target the shoulders and upper back: * **T Raise:** Lift your arms straight out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a “T” shape.", "* **Y Raise:** Lift your arms upward at about a 45° angle from your body to form a “Y” shape.", "* **I Raise:** Raise your arms straight overhead, close together, forming an “I” shape.", "Maintain a neutral spine, avoid arching your lower back, and move slowly with control.", "Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together and keeping your shoulders down away from your ears."], "sources": [{"source": "wger", "file": "C:\\Users\\kaiqu\\Desktop\\SOMMA\\datasets\\wger-master\\wger\\exercises\\fixtures\\exercise-base-data.json", "steps": ["Stand upright with feet hip-width apart, core engaged, and arms relaxed at your sides.", "From this position, perform three different arm raises to target the shoulders and upper back: * **T Raise:** Lift your arms straight out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a “T” shape.", "* **Y Raise:** Lift your arms upward at about a 45° angle from your body to form a “Y” shape.", "* **I Raise:** Raise your arms straight overhead, close together, forming an “I” shape.", "Maintain a neutral spine, avoid arching your lower back, and move slowly with control.", "Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together and keeping your shoulders down away from your ears."], "description": "Stand upright with feet hip-width apart, core engaged, and arms relaxed at your sides. From this position, perform three different arm raises to target the shoulders and upper back: * **T Raise:** Lift your arms straight out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a “T” shape. * **Y Raise:** Lift your arms upward at about a 45° angle from your body to form a “Y” shape. * **I Raise:** Raise your arms straight overhead, close together, forming an “I” shape. Maintain a neutral spine, avoid arching your lower back, and move slowly with control. Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together and keeping your shoulders down away from your ears."}], "summary": "Stand upright with feet hip-width apart, core engaged, and arms relaxed at your sides. From this position, perform three different arm raises to target the shoulders and upper back: * **T Raise:** Lift your arms straight out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a “T” shape. * **Y Raise:** Lift your arms upward at about a 45° angle from your body to form a “Y” shape. * **I Raise:** Raise your arms straight overhead, close together, forming an “I” shape. Maintain a neutral spine, avoid arching your lower back, and move slowly with control. Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together and keeping your shoulders down away from your ears.", "setup": "Stand upright with feet hip-width apart, core engaged, and arms relaxed at your sides.", "eccentric": "From this position, perform three different arm raises to target the shoulders and upper back: * **T Raise:** Lift your arms straight out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a “T” shape.", "concentric": "* **Y Raise:** Lift your arms upward at about a 45° angle from your body to form a “Y” shape. · * **I Raise:** Raise your arms straight overhead, close together, forming an “I” shape.", "regression": "Maintain a neutral spine, avoid arching your lower back, and move slowly with control.", "safety": "Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together and keeping your shoulders down away from your ears."}'::jsonb,
